09/06/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- The proposal harmonising Turkish legislation with that of the EU will be submitted to parliament this week, according to Dengir Mir Mehmet Firat, deputy chairman of the ruling Justice and Development Party. 
Firat spoke to journalists on Sunday (8 June). 
Following approval by parliament, the package will then move to the National Security Council, made up of government and military officials. 
Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan predicts it will face no problems in obtaining approval.
In other news, Erdogan spoke by phone Sunday with Israeli Prime Minister Ariel Sharon and his Palestinian counterpart, Mahmud Abbas. 
He offered Turkey's help in implementing the road map to peace, aimed at ending the Israeli-Palestinian conflict. 
(Hurriyet, Milliyet - 09/06/03; Anadolu Agency, NTV, AFP - 08/06/03)
